Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco, met with Turkish Foreign Minister Feridun Sinirlioglu to discuss U.S.-Turkish counterterrorism cooperation. They reviewed the progress of the counter-ISIL Coalition and efforts to degrade and destroy ISIL. Monaco thanked Sinirlioglu for Turkey's increased participation in the Coalition, including allowing U.S. aircraft to fly missions from Turkish airbases. They also discussed the importance of a negotiated political settlement in Syria and expanding cooperation on border security and countering the flow of foreign fighters.